                                Preamble

 The FFP (Freedom For People) License is a free and permissive license
 intended to maximize human freedom by ensuring that software,
 documentation, art, media, data, and other copyrightable works remain
 available for anyone to use, study, modify, and share.

 Version 2.0 strengthens the original v1.0 text by adding clearer
 definitions, an explicit Indemnification clause, stronger Warranty and
 Liability disclaimers with jurisdictional carve-outs, an Export
 Controls notice, explicit AI/ML training permissions, a path for
 future license versions, and a governing law provision.

 This License grants broad permission to use, copy, modify, distribute,
 and sell the Work, while requiring that recipients receive a copy of
 this License and that copyright and attribution notices are preserved.

 This License includes a patent license grant from Contributors and
 protects the commons by terminating patent rights granted under this
 License if a recipient initiates patent litigation alleging that the
 Work infringes a patent.

 The Work is provided without warranty, and the Licensor and
 Contributors disclaim liability for damages.

 The precise terms and conditions follow.

                          TERMS AND CONDITIONS

 0. Definitions.

  "This License" refers to version 2.0 of the FFP (Freedom For People)
 License.

  "Copyright" also means copyright-like laws that apply to other kinds
 of works, such as semiconductor masks.

  "Legal Entity" means the union of the acting entity and all other
 entities that control, are controlled by, or are under common control
 with that entity. For the purposes of this definition, "control" means
 (i) the power, direct or indirect, to cause the direction or
 management of such entity, whether by contract or otherwise, or
 (ii) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or more of the outstanding
 shares, or (iii) beneficial ownership of such entity.

  "Work" means the original work of authorship made available under
 this License, including software, documentation, hardware design
 files, art, data, media, or any other copyrightable subject matter,
 as indicated by a copyright notice that is included in or attached
 to the work.

  "Source Form" means the preferred form for making modifications,
 including but not limited to software source code, documentation
 source, and configuration files.

  "Object Form" means any form resulting from mechanical transformation
 or translation of a Source Form, including but not limited to compiled
 object code, generated documentation, and conversions to other media
 types.

  "Contribution" means any original work of authorship, including any
 modifications or additions to the Work or Derivative Works thereof,
 that is intentionally submitted for inclusion in the Work by a
 Contributor, whether in Source Form or Object Form, whether submitted
 by an individual or on behalf of a Legal Entity.

  "Derivative Work" means any work that is based upon the Work or any
 Contribution and for which the editorial revisions, annotations,
 elaborations, or other modifications represent, as a whole, an
 original work of authorship. For the purposes of this License,
 Derivative Works do not include works that remain separable from, or
 merely link to (or bind by name to), the interfaces of the Work and
 Derivative Works thereof.

  "Distribute" (or "Distribution") means to reproduce, publish,
 transfer, make available, or otherwise convey a copy of the Work,
 Contributions, or Derivative Works to any third party, whether in
 Source Form, Object Form, or any other form, by any means. Mere
 interaction with a user through a computer network, without transfer
 of a copy, is not Distribution.

  "You" (or "Your") means an individual or Legal Entity exercising
 permissions granted by this License.

  "Licensor" means the copyright holder(s) or the Legal Entity
 authorized by the copyright holder(s) that grants this License.

  "Contributor" means the Licensor and any individual or Legal Entity
 on behalf of whom a Contribution has been submitted to the Licensor
 and accepted for inclusion in the Work.

  "Effective Date" means the date on which You first exercise any right
 granted under this License.

