 4.2 Preservation of Notices.

 You must retain, in all copies of the Work and Derivative Works that
 You Distribute, all copyright notices, patent notices, trademark
 notices, attribution notices, and license notices that are present
 in the Source Form of the Work, except where removal is expressly
 required by applicable law.

 4.3 No Lockdown of the Licensed Work.

 When You Distribute the Work or Derivative Works, You may not impose
 legal, contractual, or technological measures — including Digital
 Rights Management (DRM) and Technical Protection Measures (TPM) —
 that effectively prevent recipients from exercising the rights
 expressly granted to them under this License with respect to the
 Work or Derivative Works.

 This section does not restrict:

   (a) agreements or technical measures unrelated to the exercise of
       rights in the Work itself;

   (b) encryption, authentication, or security measures applied to
       the Work, provided such measures do not prevent authorized
       recipients from accessing the Work under this License; or

   (c) measures required by applicable law.

 4.4 Hardware and Physical Works.

 Where the Work includes design files for hardware or physical objects,
 this License grants rights only to the extent that applicable law
 recognizes copyright or related rights in such design files. This
 License grants no patent rights in hardware except as expressly
 stated in Section 3.

