 8. Termination and Reinstatement.

 8.1 Automatic Termination.

 Your rights under this License terminate automatically and immediately,
 without notice, if You materially fail to comply with any term of this
 License, including the conditions of Section 4 (Conditions of
 Distribution) or Section 3.2 (Defensive Termination).

 8.2 Reinstatement for Cure.

 If You cease all violations of this License and cure the violation
 within thirty (30) days of becoming aware of the violation (or within
 thirty (30) days of receiving written notice from the Licensor), then
 Your license from that copyright holder is reinstated:

   (a) provisionally, unless and until the copyright holder explicitly
       and finally terminates Your license in writing; and

   (b) permanently, if the copyright holder does not provide written
       notice of the violation within sixty (60) days after the
       cessation of all violations.

 Reinstatement under Section 8.2 does not affect any right the copyright
 holder may have to seek remedies for Your violation of this License.

 8.3 Patent Termination.

 If Your license is terminated under Section 3.2 (Defensive
 Termination), it is not subject to reinstatement under Section 8.2.

