                  HOW TO APPLY THE FFP LICENSE TO YOUR WORK

 To apply the FFP (Freedom For People) License v2.0 to your Work,
 follow the steps below.

 It is recommended that you:

   1. Place a full copy of this License in a file named "LICENSE" (or
      "COPYING") in the top-level directory of your Work.

   2. Add the notice below to the main README file and/or the header
      of important source files.

   3. Ensure that all copyright, patent, attribution, and license
      notices present in the Work are preserved in any redistributed
      copies or Derivative Works, as required by Section 4.

 Replace the bracketed placeholders with your own information.

    Copyright (C) [YEAR] [FULL NAME OF LICENSOR OR ORGANIZATION]

    This Work is licensed under the FFP (Freedom For People) License,
    Version 2.0.

    A copy of this License must be included in the LICENSE file
    distributed with this Work.

    You may also obtain a copy of the License at:
    https://github.com/druvx13/FFP

    THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
    EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. SEE THE LICENSE FOR DETAILS.

    DISCLAIMER: This license was drafted with AI assistance and is
    for informational purposes only. It does not constitute legal
    advice. Consult a qualified legal professional before use.

 If your Work includes interactive user interfaces, it is recommended
 (but not required) to display a notice stating that the Work is
 licensed under the FFP License v2.0 and that it comes without warranty.

